  "extra_hunts": [
    "Hunt for password spraying against cloud identity, VPN, and exposed remote-access surfaces, then pivot from successful sign-ins into valid-account persistence, MFA changes, Azure/Entra enumeration, and cloud-resource creation.",
    "Review recruitment, aviation, defense, satellite, oil-and-gas, petrochemical, education, and government-themed lures, including malicious archive attachments, HTA links, Teams/LinkedIn social engineering, and files masquerading as policy or infrastructure documents.",
    "Hunt for APT33/Peach Sandstorm tooling and tradecraft: Tickler, POWERTON, TURNEDUP, PoshC2, Empire, RMM tools such as AnyDesk, AD Explorer snapshots, LaZagne, Mimikatz, ProcDump, SniffPass, WMI persistence, scheduled tasks, and Registry Run keys.",
    "Pivot from HTTP/S C2, Azure App Service infrastructure, non-standard HTTP ports, suspicious go-http-client authentication activity, SMB/RDP lateral movement, and FTP exfiltration into surrounding staging, credential access, and data-transfer behavior.",
    "Review destructive-risk leads separately, including DROPSHOT, SHAPESHIFT, DEADWOOD, Shamoon-adjacent tradecraft, RawDisk-style driver usage, account access removal, disk-wipe behavior, service execution, and abnormal shutdown or file-deletion sequences."
  ],
